ture-61","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"Storage is keyed, never a growing list — so a deposit's cost does **not** scale with history:"},"64":{"id":"architecture-62","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"Key"},"65":{"id":"architecture-63","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"Value"},"66":{"id":"architecture-64","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"Purpose"},"67":{"id":"architecture-65","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"`Balance(stealth_pk, token)`"},"68":{"id":"architecture-66","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"`i128`"},"69":{"id":"architecture-67","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"Per-(key, token) balance. Not a mixer — each stealth key has its own isolated balance."},"70":{"id":"architecture-68","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"`Nonce(stealth_pk)`"},"71":{"id":"architecture-69","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"`u64`"},"72":{"id":"architecture-70","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"Replay protection; must strictly increase."},"73":{"id":"architecture-71","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"`Announcement(index)`"},"74":{"id":"architecture-72","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"`AnnouncementEntry`"},"75":{"id":"architecture-73","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"One announcement per own keyed entry — **O(1) append**, no history rewrite."},"76":{"id":"architecture-74","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"`AnnouncementCount`"},"77":{"id":"architecture-75","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"`u64`"},"78":{"id":"architecture-76","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"Total announcements; also the next index."},"79":{"id":"architecture-77","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#storage-layout","content":"All entries are **persistent** storage. TTLs are extended on write and, notably, **on read**: `get_balance` and `get_nonce` bump a live entry's TTL back up to the ceiling. That means a passively-scanning recipient keeps their own balance alive without ever writing."},"80":{"id":"architecture-78","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#authorization-model","content":"Two different mechanisms, deliberately:"},"81":{"id":"architecture-79","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#authorization-model","content":"**`deposit`** uses `sender.require_auth()` — the sender is a normal Stellar account, so standard Soroban auth applies."},"82":{"id":"architecture-80","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#authorization-model","content":"**`withdraw`*&#x2A; uses &#x2A;*`env.crypto().ed25519_verify`** on an explicit message — *not* `require_auth`. A stealth key is not a Stellar account and has no auth entry, so the contract verifies a raw signature instead. This is what lets **anyone** (a relayer, a friend, a fee-payer) submit the transaction on the recipient's behalf without being the recipient."},"83":{"id":"architecture-81","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#the-withdraw-message","content":"The signed message must be byte-identical between Rust and TypeScript:"},"84":{"id":"architecture-82","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#the-withdraw-message","content":"The trailing **contract address** and **network id** (= `SHA-256(network passphrase)`, matching the on-chain `env.ledger().network_id()`) bind the signature to a single deployment on a single network, preventing cross-deployment and cross-network replay."},"85":{"id":"architecture-83","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#reentrancy-safety","content":"`withdraw` follows **checks-effects-interactions**: the nonce and balance are committed to storage **before** the external SAC `transfer` call, so a malicious token contract cannot re-enter and replay the withdrawal."},"86":{"id":"architecture-84","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#stellar-asset-contract-sac","content":"The contract moves value through the standard token interface (`soroban_sdk::token::Client`), so it works with any **Stellar Asset Contract** — the contract that exposes a classic Stellar asset (native XLM, USDC, any issued asset) to Soroban. Cross-contract calls are limited to these SAC `transfer` calls:"},"87":{"id":"architecture-85","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#stellar-asset-contract-sac","content":"`deposit` → `transfer(sender → contract)`"},"88":{"id":"architecture-86","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#stellar-asset-contract-sac","content":"`withdraw` → `transfer(contract → destination)`"},"89":{"id":"architecture-87","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#stellar-asset-contract-sac","content":"The SDK resolves an asset string to its SAC address with `resolveTokenAddress`, and `labelForToken` reverses the deterministic native-XLM SAC id back to the label `XLM` for display."},"90":{"id":"architecture-88","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"**1. Send** (`PoolAdapter.send`)"},"91":{"id":"architecture-89","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Decode the meta-address → `(K_spend, K_view)`"},"92":{"id":"architecture-90","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Draw a random 32-byte ephemeral `r`; derive `P`, `R`, `view_tag`"},"93":{"id":"architecture-91","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Resolve the asset to a SAC address; convert the amount to stroops"},"94":{"id":"architecture-92","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Build the `deposit(...)` invocation, `prepareTransaction`, sign (local secret or external signer), submit"},"95":{"id":"architecture-93","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Interpret the RPC result: only `SUCCESS` / `PENDING` / `DUPLICATE` count as landed; anything else throws (a `TRY_AGAIN_LATER` becomes a retryable error rather than a false success)"},"96":{"id":"architecture-94","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"**2. Scan** (`PoolAdapter.scan`)"},"97":{"id":"architecture-95","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Read `get_announcement_count()` — a cheap freshness check that lets a caller skip a full scan"},"98":{"id":"architecture-96","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Page `get_announcements(start, limit)` from the cursor (200 per page)"},"99":{"id":"architecture-97","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Run the two-pass scan: ECDH + view-tag filter, then full derivation on tag matches"},"100":{"id":"architecture-98","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"For each match, read `get_balance` and drop zero balances"},"101":{"id":"architecture-99","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Return payments plus an advanced cursor (the announcement index)"},"102":{"id":"architecture-100","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"**3. Claim / withdraw** (`PoolAdapter.withdraw`)"},"103":{"id":"architecture-101","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Find the announcement matching the stealth address"},"104":{"id":"architecture-102","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"`recoverStealthPrivateKey` → the raw stealth scalar"},"105":{"id":"architecture-103","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Read `get_balance` and `get_nonce`; the new nonce is `current + 1`"},"106":{"id":"architecture-104","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Build the withdraw message; sign it with `signWithStealthKey`"},"107":{"id":"architecture-105","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Build the `withdraw(...)` invocation sourced by the **fee payer**"},"108":{"id":"architecture-106","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"**Restore-aware prepare** (below)"},"109":{"id":"architecture-107","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-pool-send--scan--claim","content":"Sign the fee-payer leg; submit directly to RPC, or POST to the relayer's `/relay` for a fee-bump"},"110":{"id":"architecture-108","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#restore-aware-preparation","content":"`server.prepareTransaction` only throws on a simulation *error* — it ignores `sim.restorePreamble`. If the recipient's `Balance`/`Nonce` entry has archived, a bare prepare would assemble the withdraw over an archived footprint: it submits, fails on-chain, and `get_balance` still shows the funds — an opaque brick."},"111":{"id":"architecture-109","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#restore-aware-preparation","content":"`prepareWithRestore` (`packages/sdk/src/methods/restore.ts`) fixes this in three steps. On `isSimulationRestore` it builds and submits a `RestoreFootprintOp` from the preamble, then waits for it to land. Because that restore consumes the fee payer's next sequence number, it then **re-fetches the account and rebuilds the invocation on the fresh sequence**. Only then does it re-simulate. Without the rebuild, the withdraw would collide at an already-consumed sequence (`txBAD_SEQ`)."},"112":{"id":"architecture-110","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-account-method","content":"The `account` method never touches the contract:"},"113":{"id":"architecture-111","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-account-method","content":"**Send** — a classic transaction with the ephemeral `R` in a 32-byte `MemoHash`. Native XLM lands via `CreateAccount`/`Payment`; a token lands as a `CreateClaimableBalance` naming the stealth address as claimant."},"114":{"id":"architecture-112","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-account-method","content":"**Scan** — page Horizon transactions; for each hash-memo tx, decode the memo as a candidate `R`, derive the stealth address, and look for an operation whose destination matches. The destination match **is** the verification — no view tag needed."},"115":{"id":"architecture-113","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#data-flow-account-method","content":"**Claim** — sign with the recovered stealth key: `AccountMerge` (full sweep) or `Payment` (partial) for XLM; `ChangeTrust` + `ClaimClaimableBalance` (+ optional exit) for a token, or a relayer-sponsored claim."},"116":{"id":"architecture-114","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"Concern"},"117":{"id":"architecture-115","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"Location"},"118":{"id":"architecture-116","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"Signature/message binding (anti-replay)"},"119":{"id":"architecture-117","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"`contracts/registry/src/lib.rs` + `packages/sdk/src/soroban.ts`"},"120":{"id":"architecture-118","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"Reentrancy ordering"},"121":{"id":"architecture-119","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"`contracts/registry/src/lib.rs` (`withdraw`)"},"122":{"id":"architecture-120","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"State-archival restore"},"123":{"id":"architecture-121","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"`packages/sdk/src/methods/restore.ts`"},"124":{"id":"architecture-122","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"Malicious-relayer defence"},"125":{"id":"architecture-123","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"`packages/sdk/src/methods/account.ts` (`verifySponsoredClaimXdr`)"},"126":{"id":"architecture-124","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"Small-subgroup / torsion rejection"},"127":{"id":"architecture-125","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"`packages/crypto/src/ed25519.ts` (`validatePoint`)"},"128":{"id":"architecture-126","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"Credit accounting, idempotency"},"129":{"id":"architecture-127","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"`packages/relayer/src/ledger.ts`"},"130":{"id":"architecture-128","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#next-steps","content":"Delivery Methods — choosing between `pool` and `account`"},"131":{"id":"architecture-129","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#next-steps","content":"SDK Reference — the API over this architecture"},"132":{"id":"architecture-130","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#next-steps","content":"Relayer — the service in the diagram's right-h