71","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#local-state","content":"`horizon-cursor-<network>`"},"307":{"id":"cli-172","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#local-state","content":"Account-method Horizon paging cursor"},"308":{"id":"cli-173","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#local-state","content":"`horizon-payments-<network>.json`"},"309":{"id":"cli-174","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#local-state","content":"Discovered account-method payments (deduplicated)"},"310":{"id":"cli-175","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#local-state","content":"The keystore itself defaults to `~/.shade-keys.json`."},"311":{"id":"cli-176","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#next-steps","content":"Getting Started — install and first run"},"312":{"id":"cli-177","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#next-steps","content":"Delivery Methods — what `--method` actually changes"},"313":{"id":"cli-178","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#next-steps","content":"SDK Reference — the programmatic equivalent"},"314":{"id":"cli-179","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#next-steps","content":"FAQ & Troubleshooting — common command failures"},"315":{"id":"concepts","page_id":"concepts","type":"page","content":"Core Concepts","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Learn"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts"},"316":{"id":"concepts-0","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts","content":"How stealth addresses work on Stellar: DKSAP, view and spend keys, meta-addresses, view tags, and the ed25519 math behind them."},"317":{"id":"concepts-1","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#two-keys-not-one","content":"Two keys, not one"},"318":{"id":"concepts-2","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#meta-address","content":"Meta-address"},"319":{"id":"concepts-3","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#stealth-address","content":"Stealth address"},"320":{"id":"concepts-4","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#ephemeral-key-r-and-shared-secret-s","content":"Ephemeral key (R) and shared secret (S)"},"321":{"id":"concepts-5","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#view-tag","content":"View tag"},"322":{"id":"concepts-6","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"The math"},"323":{"id":"concepts-7","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#why-the-ecdh-runs-client-side","content":"Why the ECDH runs client-side"},"324":{"id":"concepts-8","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#getting-your-keys--four-ways","content":"Getting your keys — four ways"},"325":{"id":"concepts-9","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"Announcement"},"326":{"id":"concepts-10","page_id":"concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/concepts#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"327":{"id":"concepts-11","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts","content":"\\{/\\* adapted from shade\\@36217c4 docs/02-core-concepts.md \\*/}"},"328":{"id":"concepts-12","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts","content":"import \\{ Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout';"},"329":{"id":"concepts-13","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts","content":"Shade implements **DKSAP** — the Dual-Key Stealth Address Protocol — on ed25519. This page defines every term used across the rest of the docs, in plain English first, with the exact math underneath."},"330":{"id":"concepts-14","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#two-keys-not-one","content":"Most wallets have one key that does everything. Shade splits your identity into **two** key pairs, which is what makes safe scanning possible:"},"331":{"id":"concepts-15","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#two-keys-not-one","content":"**View key** — lets someone *find* payments sent to you. It can **see** but **cannot spend**. Safe to hand to a phone, a server, or a watch-only scanning service."},"332":{"id":"concepts-16","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#two-keys-not-one","content":"**Spend key** — required to actually *move* the money. This one never leaves you."},"333":{"id":"concepts-17","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#two-keys-not-one","content":"Each key has a public and a private half:"},"334":{"id":"concepts-18","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#two-keys-not-one","content":"The **public** spend + view keys go *into the meta-address you give out*, so a sender can do the math to create your one-time address."},"335":{"id":"concepts-19","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#two-keys-not-one","content":"The **private** spend + view keys stay *with you*: the private view key **detects** incoming payments, the private spend key **spends** them."},"336":{"id":"concepts-20","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#meta-address","content":"Your **meta-address** is the public halves of both keys, bundled and encoded:"},"337":{"id":"concepts-21","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#meta-address","content":"It is **not a Stellar account** — you cannot send funds to it directly. It is only an input a sender uses to *compute* a one-time address. Share it freely: profile, DM, business card."},"338":{"id":"concepts-22","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#stealth-address","content":"A **stealth address** is the one-time destination a sender derives from your meta-address. It's a normal Stellar `G...` address, but nobody can link it back to your meta-address without your view key."},"339":{"id":"concepts-23","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#stealth-address","content":"In the `pool` method the stealth address is never a real Stellar account — it's a **key** the contract uses to track your balance. In the `account` method it *is* a real, funded one-time account. See Delivery Methods."},"340":{"id":"concepts-24","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#ephemeral-key-r-and-shared-secret-s","content":"For every payment, the sender picks a fresh random scalar `r` and publishes `R = r·G` (the **ephemeral public key**). Both sides can then compute the same **shared secret** without talking to each other:"},"341":{"id":"concepts-25","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#ephemeral-key-r-and-shared-secret-s","content":"Sender: `S = r · K_view`"},"342":{"id":"concepts-26","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#ephemeral-key-r-and-shared-secret-s","content":"Receiver: `S = k_view · R`"},"343":{"id":"concepts-27","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#ephemeral-key-r-and-shared-secret-s","content":"This is **ECDH** (Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman) — the standard trick that lets two parties arrive at the same secret without ever transmitting it. `S` is what makes the stealth address derivable by you and nobody else."},"344":{"id":"concepts-28","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#view-tag","content":"The **view tag** is a single byte — `SHA256(S)[0]` — published alongside each announcement. It's a fast-path filter: if the tag doesn't match, the announcement definitely isn't yours and you can skip the rest of the check."},"345":{"id":"concepts-29","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#view-tag","content":"**What it actually saves.** Computing the tag still requires the shared secret, which means a full ECDH (`scalarMult`) per announcement — that cost is unavoidable and dominates scanning. The view tag only lets you skip the *extra&#x2A; address-derivation step for the \\~255/256 of announcements that don't match. Measured end-to-end speedup: &#x2A;*\\~2×**."},"346":{"id":"concepts-30","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#view-tag","content":"> Only the `pool` method uses view tags. The `account` method matches on the derived destination address directly, which *is* the full verification."},"347":{"id":"concepts-31","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"**Meta-address generation (receiver)**"},"348":{"id":"concepts-32","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"Generate two random scalars `k_spend`, `k_view` ∈ `[0, L-1]`"},"349":{"id":"concepts-33","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"Compute `K_spend = k_spend · G`, `K_view = k_view · G`"},"350":{"id":"concepts-34","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"Meta-address = `(K_spend, K_view)`"},"351":{"id":"concepts-35","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"**Stealth address derivation (sender)**"},"352":{"id":"concepts-36","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"Pick random ephemeral scalar `r`"},"353":{"id":"concepts-37","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"`R = r · G`"},"354":{"id":"concepts-38","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"`S = r · K_view`"},"355":{"id":"concepts-39","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"`s = SHA256(S) mod L`"},"356":{"id":"concepts-40","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"`P_stealth = K_spend + s · G`"},"357":{"id":"concepts-41","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"`view_tag = SHA256(S)[0]`"},"358":{"id":"concepts-42","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"**Scanning (receiver)**"},"359":{"id":"concepts-43","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"For each announcement: `S = k_view · R`"},"360":{"id":"concepts-44","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"Filter: does `SHA256(S)[0]` equal the published view tag?"},"361":{"id":"concepts-45","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"On a match: `P = K_spend + SHA256(S)·G`"},"362":{"id":"concepts-46","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"Verify `P` equals the announced stealth address"},"363":{"id":"concepts-47","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"**Private key recovery (receiver)**"},"364":{"id":"concepts-48","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"`S = k_view · R`"},"365":{"id":"concepts-49","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"`s = SHA256(S) mod L`"},"366":{"id":"concepts-50","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"`p_stealth = k_spend + s mod L`"},"367":{"id":"concepts-51","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"**Curve parameters**"},"368":{"id":"concepts-52","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"Curve: ed25519"},"369":{"id":"concepts-53","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#the-math","content":"Order: `L = 2^252 + 27742317777372353535851937790883648493`"},"370":{"id":"concepts-54","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#why-the-ecdh-runs-client-side","content":"Stellar's smart-contract environment doesn't offer the specific curve operation the ECDH needs, so that math runs **on your device**, not on-chain. The contract never sees your keys — it only checks a signature."},"371":{"id":"concepts-55","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#getting-your-keys--four-ways","content":"**Random** — fresh keys, back them up yourself."},"372":{"id":"concepts-56","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#getting-your-keys--four-ways","content":"**BIP-39 mnemonic** — 12 words you write down; recover on any device."},"373":{"id":"concepts-57","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#getting-your-keys--four-ways","content":"**HD derivation** — deterministic, via domain-separated SHA-256."},"374":{"id":"concepts-58","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#getting-your-keys--four-ways","content":"**From your wallet's signature** — sign one fixed message with your Stellar wallet and Shade derives your stealth keys from that signature. Same wallet + same scope → the same keys every time, so there is nothing extra to store or back up. This is the \"keyless\" path."},"375":{"id":"concepts-59","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#getting-your-keys--four-ways","content":"**Trade-off for method 4:** your wallet effectively *is* your stealth-key backup. If the wallet is compromised, so are the stealth keys. That is the accepted deal for keyless recovery. Also: never sign the derivation message anywhere you don't trust — anyone who obtains that signature can derive (and thus control) your stealth keys."},"376":{"id":"concepts-60","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#getting-your-keys--four-ways","content":"**Key scoping.** The `appId` and `keyScope` are folded into the signed message, so different applications derive independent keys. They must **match across every tool** that derives from the same wallet, or you'll get different, non-interoperable keys. Defaults: `appId = 'default'`, `keyScope = 'stealth'` (SDK constants `DEFAULT_APP_ID` / `DEFAULT_KEY_SCOPE`; the CLI's `--app-id` / `--key-scope` default to the same values)."},"377":{"id":"concepts-61","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"An **announcement** is the on-chain record that lets you discover a payment. In the `pool` method it's a contract storage entry created **atomically with the deposit** — no deposit, no announcement, which makes announcement spam impossible. It carries:"},"378":{"id":"concepts-62","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"Field"},"379":{"id":"concepts-63","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"Meaning"},"380":{"id":"concepts-64","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"`ephemeral_pk`"},"381":{"id":"concepts-65","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"The 32-byte `R`"},"382":{"id":"concepts-66","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"`view_tag`"},"383":{"id":"concepts-67","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"The one-byte fast-path filter (stored as `u32`)"},"384":{"id":"concepts-68","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"`stealth_pk`"},"385":{"id":"concepts-69","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"The 32-byte derived stealth public key"},"386":{"id":"concepts-70","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"`token`"},"387":{"id":"concepts-71","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"The SAC token address that was deposited"},"388":{"id":"concepts-72","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"`amount`"},"389":{"id":"concepts-73","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"Amount deposited, in the token's smallest unit"},"390":{"id":"concepts-74","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"`sequence`"},"391":{"id":"concepts-75","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"Ledger sequence at deposit time"},"392":{"id":"concepts-76","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#announcement","content":"In the `account` method there is no contract announcement: the ephemeral key `R&#x60; rides in the transaction's &#x2A;*`MemoHash`**, and discovery means paging Horizon."},"393":{"id":"concepts-77","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#next-steps","content":"Architecture — how these concepts map onto components"},"394":{"id":"concepts-78","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#next-steps","content":"Delivery Methods — where `pool` and `account` differ"},"395":{"id":"concepts-79","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#next-steps","content":"SDK Reference — the functions that implement all of this"},"396":{"id":"concepts-80","page_id":"concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/concepts#next-steps","content":"Security — what the cryptography does and does not guarantee"},"397":{"id":"delivery-methods","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"page","content":"Delivery Methods","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Learn"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods"},"398":{"id":"delivery-methods-0","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods","content":"Compare Shade's delivery methods: the Soroban pool contract versus a direct one-time Stellar account — where funds sit, what they cost, and how you claim them."},"399":{"id":"delivery-methods-1","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"The three slots"},"400":{"id":"delivery-methods-2","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"`pool` — the Soroban contract"},"401":{"id":"delivery-methods-3","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods#account--a-direct-one-time-account","content":"`account` — a direct one-time account"},"402":{"id":"delivery-methods-4","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods#native-xlm","content":"Native XLM"},"403":{"id":"delivery-methods-5","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"Tokens (USDC and friends)"},"404":{"id":"delivery-methods-6","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods#auto--letting-the-client-choose","content":"`auto` — letting the client choose"},"405":{"id":"delivery-methods-7","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods#spp--reserved-not-implemented","content":"`spp` — reserved, not implemented"},"406":{"id":"delivery-methods-8","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"Choosing"},"407":{"id":"delivery-methods-9","page_id":"delivery-methods","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/delivery-methods#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"408":{"id":"delivery-methods-10","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods","content":"\\{/\\* adapted from shade\\@36217c4 docs/04-delivery-methods.md \\*/}"},"409":{"id":"delivery-methods-11","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods","content":"import \\{ Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout';"},"410":{"id":"delivery-methods-12","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods","content":"The same meta-address works with more than one \"delivery method\" — the mechanism that actually carries money to the recipient. They differ in where funds sit, what they cost, and how you claim them. This page compares them and tells you which to pick."},"411":{"id":"delivery-methods-13","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"`DeliveryMethod = 'pool' | 'account' | 'spp'`"},"412":{"id":"delivery-methods-14","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**pool**"},"413":{"id":"delivery-methods-15","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**account**"},"414":{"id":"delivery-methods-16","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**spp**"},"415":{"id":"delivery-methods-17","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**Status**"},"416":{"id":"delivery-methods-18","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"✅ Implemented"},"417":{"id":"delivery-methods-19","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"✅ Implemented"},"418":{"id":"delivery-methods-20","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"⏳ Reserved slot — *not built*"},"419":{"id":"delivery-methods-21","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**Where funds sit**"},"420":{"id":"delivery-methods-22","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"Shared Soroban **pool contract**, keyed by your stealth key"},"421":{"id":"delivery-methods-23","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"A one-time real Stellar **account** / claimable balance"},"422":{"id":"delivery-methods-24","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"—"},"423":{"id":"delivery-methods-25","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**New account created?**"},"424":{"id":"delivery-methods-26","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**No** — no \\~1 XLM reserve locked"},"425":{"id":"delivery-methods-27","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**Yes** — \\~1 XLM base reserve required"},"426":{"id":"delivery-methods-28","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"—"},"427":{"id":"delivery-methods-29","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**Assets**"},"428":{"id":"delivery-methods-30","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"Any SAC token (XLM, USDC, …)"},"429":{"id":"delivery-methods-31","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"Native XLM, or any classic/SAC asset (as a claimable balance)"},"430":{"id":"delivery-methods-32","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"—"},"431":{"id":"delivery-methods-33","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**Discovery**"},"432":{"id":"delivery-methods-34","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"Contract **announcements** + **view-tag** fast path (\\~2×)"},"433":{"id":"delivery-methods-35","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**Horizon** paging for the ephemeral key in a `MemoHash`, then destination match (no view tag)"},"434":{"id":"delivery-methods-36","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"—"},"435":{"id":"delivery-methods-37","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**Claim**"},"436":{"id":"delivery-methods-38","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"Signature-verified `withdraw` — **no Stellar account needed**"},"437":{"id":"delivery-methods-39","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"Sign with the recovered stealth key, or a relayer-sponsored payout"},"438":{"id":"delivery-methods-40","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"—"},"439":{"id":"delivery-methods-41","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**Cost profile**"},"440":{"id":"delivery-methods-42","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"Soroban invocation fee (\\~0.01 XLM)"},"441":{"id":"delivery-methods-43","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"\\~1 XLM reserve (native) or \\~1.5 XLM fronted (token)"},"442":{"id":"delivery-methods-44","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"—"},"443":{"id":"delivery-methods-45","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#the-three-slots","content":"**Rule of thumb:*&#x2A; use &#x2A;*`pool`*&#x2A; for the best privacy/cost trade-off and any token — you never need a funded account to claim. Use &#x2A;*`account`** for the simplest path that works with vanilla Horizon tooling."},"444":{"id":"delivery-methods-46","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"Money is deposited into the pool contract and tracked under `Balance(stealth_pk, token)`. No Stellar account is ever created for the stealth key, so **no \\~1 XLM MBR is locked**."},"445":{"id":"delivery-methods-47","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"The deposit and its announcement are written **atomically** — no deposit, no announcement — which makes announcement spam impossible."},"446":{"id":"delivery-methods-48","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"**Claiming** calls `withdraw(...)` with an ed25519 signature over the withdraw message. Because authorization is a signature rather than `require_auth`, *anyone* can submit the transaction for you. Two ways to pay the Soroban fee:"},"447":{"id":"delivery-methods-49","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"**Direct** — you supply a fee-payer account and submit to RPC yourself."},"448":{"id":"delivery-methods-50","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"**Relayer fee-bump** — POST to the relayer's `/relay`; it pays the fee, so you never reveal a funded account of your own. See Relayer."},"449":{"id":"delivery-methods-51","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"You may withdraw the **full balance or a partial amount** (`opts.amount`)."},"450":{"id":"delivery-methods-52","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"**Requirements and caveats**"},"451":{"id":"delivery-methods-53","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"`contractId` is **required** whenever the pool method is enabled — there is a built-in default only for `local`. A `testnet` client with pool enabled and no explicit `contractId` throws `ContractIdRequiredError`."},"452":{"id":"delivery-methods-54","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"The withdrawal **destination must be an existing Stellar account** (it needs its own reserve to exist)."},"453":{"id":"delivery-methods-55","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#pool--the-soroban-contract","content":"**Not a mixer.** The deposit and the withdraw both name the same `stealth_pk` on-chain, so the *flow* remains traceable; only the link to your identity is hidden."},"454":{"id":"delivery-methods-56","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#account--a-direct-one-time-account","content":"Money goes to a real, one-time Stellar account. The ephemeral key `R` travels in the transaction's 32-byte `MemoHash`; discovery derives the stealth address from `(k_view, R)` and looks for an operation whose destination matches. That destination match **is** the full DKSAP verification, so no view tag is needed."},"455":{"id":"delivery-methods-57","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#account--a-direct-one-time-account","content":"**For developers.** `normalizeDestination` in `packages/sdk/src/methods/account.ts`, via `MuxedAccount.fromAddress(address, '0').baseAccount().accountId()`. Note this normalizes for **matching only** — Shade never *derives* a muxed stealth address; the sender always creates a plain `G...` one-time account. </Callout>"},"456":{"id":"delivery-methods-58","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#native-xlm","content":"Sent via `CreateAccount` (falling back to `Payment` if the account already exists). The amount **must be strictly greater than 1 XLM** — below that the account cannot meet its base reserve — otherwise you get `MinimumAmountError`."},"457":{"id":"delivery-methods-59","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#native-xlm","content":"Claiming:"},"458":{"id":"delivery-methods-60","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#native-xlm","content":"**Full sweep** (default, `merge: true`) — `AccountMerge` delivers the entire balance including the reserve to your destination."},"459":{"id":"delivery-methods-61","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#native-xlm","content":"**Partial** (`merge: false`) — a `Payment` that leaves the account open. The account must retain &#x2A;*2× the base reserve (1.0 XLM)** plus the fee; an over-large request throws `ClaimAmountError` with the maximum named."},"460":{"id":"delivery-methods-62","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#native-xlm","content":"Either can be relayer fee-bumped."},"461":{"id":"delivery-methods-63","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"One transaction with two operations: `CreateAccount(stealth, 1.5001 XLM)` to open the account with trustline headroom, then `CreateClaimableBalance(asset, amount, claimant: stealth)`. The sender fronts those reserves:"},"462":{"id":"delivery-methods-64","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"Portion"},"463":{"id":"delivery-methods-65","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"Purpose"},"464":{"id":"delivery-methods-66","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"\\~1 XLM"},"465":{"id":"delivery-methods-67","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"Base account reserve"},"466":{"id":"delivery-methods-68","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"\\~0.5 XLM"},"467":{"id":"delivery-methods-69","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"Trustline reserve headroom"},"468":{"id":"delivery-methods-70","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"\\~0.0001 XLM"},"469":{"id":"delivery-methods-71","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"Fee slack"},"470":{"id":"delivery-methods-72","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"The 0.5 XLM claimable-balance reserve returns to the **sender** when the balance is claimed."},"471":{"id":"delivery-methods-73","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"Claiming a token has two paths:"},"472":{"id":"delivery-methods-74","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"**Self-funded** — the stealth account exists and can pay: `ChangeTrust` → `ClaimClaimableBalance` → (optional full exit: `Payment` → `ChangeTrust(limit 0)` → `AccountMerge`)."},"473":{"id":"delivery-methods-75","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"**Sponsored** (`sponsored: true`, or automatically when the account stub is missing) — the relayer fronts the reserves under a **sponsorship sandwich** (a Stellar pattern where operations are wrapped between `BeginSponsoringFutureReserves` and `EndSponsoringFutureReserves`, so the sponsor pays the reserves instead of the account itself) and co-signs, so you can cash out to a **fresh, unfunded address**. See Relayer."},"474":{"id":"delivery-methods-76","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#tokens-usdc-and-friends","content":"**Requirement:** the destination must already **trust the asset**, or you get `DestinationTrustlineError` before anything is submitted."},"475":{"id":"delivery-methods-77","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#auto--letting-the-client-choose","content":"`method: 'auto'` is not a fourth method; it resolves to a real one at call time:"},"476":{"id":"delivery-methods-78","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#auto--letting-the-client-choose","content":"> native asset **AND** amount > 1 **AND** `'account'&#x60; enabled → &#x2A;*`account`*&#x2A;; otherwise → &#x2A;*`pool`**."},"477":{"id":"delivery-methods-79","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#auto--letting-the-client-choose","content":"There is deliberately **no implicit default**: every `send()` must pass a method (or `'auto'`), or it throws `MethodRequiredError`. The privacy trade-off should always be a conscious choice."},"478":{"id":"delivery-methods-80","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#spp--reserved-not-implemented","content":"`spp` is a **reserved enum slot** for a possible future integration with a *separate, external* Stellar private-payments effort. It implements the full adapter surface so an application could opt in later with zero API changes — but &#x2A;*every method throws `MethodNotAvailableError`** today."},"479":{"id":"delivery-methods-81","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#spp--reserved-not-implemented","content":"**Shade does not build `spp`, and it is not on the roadmap.** It exists only as a hook."},"480":{"id":"delivery-methods-82","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"If you want…"},"481":{"id":"delivery-methods-83","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"Use"},"482":{"id":"delivery-methods-84","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"Best privacy/cost trade-off; any SAC token"},"483":{"id":"delivery-methods-85","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"`pool`"},"484":{"id":"delivery-methods-86","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"To claim without ever having a funded account"},"485":{"id":"delivery-methods-87","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"`pool` (fee-bumped) or `account` + sponsored claim"},"486":{"id":"delivery-methods-88","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"To avoid locking \\~1 XLM per payment"},"487":{"id":"delivery-methods-89","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"`pool`"},"488":{"id":"delivery-methods-90","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"Compatibility with plain Horizon tooling"},"489":{"id":"delivery-methods-91","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"`account`"},"490":{"id":"delivery-methods-92","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"Simple XLM transfer with a familiar on-chain shape"},"491":{"id":"delivery-methods-93","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#choosing","content":"`account`"},"492":{"id":"delivery-methods-94","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#next-steps","content":"Core Concepts — what a view tag and announcement actually are"},"493":{"id":"delivery-methods-95","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#next-steps","content":"Architecture — the data flow behind each method"},"494":{"id":"delivery-methods-96","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#next-steps","content":"SDK Reference — `SendOpts` / `ClaimOpts` for each method"},"495":{"id":"delivery-methods-97","page_id":"delivery-methods","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/delivery-methods#next-steps","content":"Relayer — fee-bumping and sponsored claims"},"496":{"id":"faq","page_id":"faq","type":"page","content":"FAQ & Troubleshooting","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Trust"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq"},"497":{"id":"faq-0","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq","content":"Common Shade questions and an error-by-error guide: what each typed error means, why it fired, and how to fix it."},"498":{"id":"faq-1","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#faq","content":"FAQ"},"499":{"id":"faq-2","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#is-shade-a-mixer","content":"Is Shade a mixer?"},"500":{"id":"faq-3","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#can-i-send-money-directly-to-a-meta-address","content":"Can I send money directly to a meta-address?"},"501":{"id":"faq-4","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#does-the-money-go-to-my-real-account","content":"Does the money go to my real account?"},"502":{"id":"faq-5","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#is-the-view-tag-really-a-25-speedup","content":"Is the view tag really a 25× speedup?"},"503":{"id":"faq-6","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#do-i-need-a-funded-account-to-receive-money","content":"Do I need a funded account to receive money?"},"504":{"id":"faq-7","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#can-i-claim-to-a-brand-new-empty-address","content":"Can I claim to a brand-new, empty address?"},"505":{"id":"faq-8","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#is-my-keystore-encrypted","content":"Is my keystore encrypted?"},"506":{"id":"faq-9","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#can-i-revoke-a-view-key-i-shared","content":"Can I revoke a view key I shared?"},"507":{"id":"faq-10","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#is-this-safe-for-mainnet","content":"Is this safe for mainnet?"},"508":{"id":"faq-11","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#what-is-spp","content":"What is `spp`?"},"509":{"id":"faq-12","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#troubleshooting-by-error","content":"Troubleshooting by error"},"510":{"id":"faq-13","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#methodrequirederror","content":"`MethodRequiredError`"},"511":{"id":"faq-14","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#contractidrequirederror","content":"`ContractIdRequiredError`"},"512":{"id":"faq-15","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#methodnotenablederror","content":"`MethodNotEnabledError`"},"513":{"id":"faq-16","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#methodnotavailableerror","content":"`MethodNotAvailableError`"},"514":{"id":"faq-17","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#minimumamounterror","content":"`MinimumAmountError`"},"515":{"id":"faq-18","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#claimamounterror","content":"`ClaimAmountError`"},"516":{"id":"faq-19","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#nobalanceerror","content":"`NoBalanceError`"},"517":{"id":"faq-20","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#announcementnotfounderror","content":"`AnnouncementNotFoundError`"},"518":{"id":"faq-21","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#stealthaccountnotfounderror","content":"`StealthAccountNotFoundError`"},"519":{"id":"faq-22","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#destinationtrustlineerror","content":"`DestinationTrustlineError`"},"520":{"id":"faq-23","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#feepayerrequirederror","content":"`FeePayerRequiredError`"},"521":{"id":"faq-24","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#feepayeraddressrequirederror","content":"`FeePayerAddressRequiredError`"},"522":{"id":"faq-25","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#sponsoredclaimmismatcherror","content":"`SponsoredClaimMismatchError`"},"523":{"id":"faq-26","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#entryarchivedrestoringerror","content":"`EntryArchivedRestoringError`"},"524":{"id":"faq-27","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#transactionretryableerror","content":"`TransactionRetryableError`"},"525":{"id":"faq-28","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#wrongpassworderror--keystore-is-encrypted-but-no-password-provided","content":"`WrongPasswordError` / \"Keystore is encrypted but no password provided\""},"526":{"id":"faq-29","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#sessionintegrityerror","content":"`SessionIntegrityError`"},"527":{"id":"faq-30","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#invalidmetaaddress","content":"`InvalidMetaAddress`"},"528":{"id":"faq-31","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#common-non-error-problems","content":"Common non-error problems"},"529":{"id":"faq-32","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#i-scanned-but-see-nothing","content":"\"I scanned but see nothing\""},"530":{"id":"faq-33","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#balance-shows-less-than-scan-found","content":"\"`balance` shows less than `scan` found\""},"531":{"id":"faq-34","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#my-withdraw-signature-is-rejected-by-the-contract","content":"\"My withdraw signature is rejected by the contract\""},"532":{"id":"faq-35","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#the-relayer-returns-402-insufficient_credit","content":"\"The relayer returns 402 `insufficient_credit`\""},"533":{"id":"faq-36","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#the-relayer-returns-401","content":"\"The relayer returns 401\""},"534":{"id":"faq-37","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#the-relayer-returns-429","content":"\"The relayer returns 429\""},"535":{"id":"faq-38","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#my-keys-dont-match-between-the-cli-and-the-sdk","content":"\"My keys don't match between the CLI and the SDK\""},"536":{"id":"faq-39","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#different-keys-every-time-i-derive-from-my-wallet","content":"\"Different keys every time I derive from my wallet\""},"537":{"id":"faq-40","page_id":"faq","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/faq#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"538":{"id":"faq-41","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq","content":"\\{/\\* adapted from shade\\@36217c4 docs/10-faq-troubleshooting.md \\*/}"},"539":{"id":"faq-42","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq","content":"Common questions, and an error-by-error guide to what went wrong and how to fix it."},"540":{"id":"faq-43","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#is-shade-a-mixer","content":"**No.** Each stealth key has its own isolated balance in the pool contract, and both the deposit and the withdrawal name that same key on-chain. The *flow* of funds stays traceable. Shade hides **who** the recipient is, not that money moved."},"541":{"id":"faq-44","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#can-i-send-money-directly-to-a-meta-address","content":"No. A meta-address is not a Stellar account — it's just two public keys bundled together. Senders use it to *compute* a fresh one-time stealth address for each payment."},"542":{"id":"faq-45","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#does-the-money-go-to-my-real-account","content":"No. In the `pool` method funds sit in the contract, keyed by a one-time stealth public key derived from your meta-address. Your real address only appears when *you* choose it as a withdrawal destination — which is why it should be a fresh address, and why the relayer should pay the fee."},"543":{"id":"faq-46","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#is-the-view-tag-really-a-25-speedup","content":"No — that figure describes the isolated address-derivation step, not scanning end-to-end. Computing a view tag still requires a full ECDH per announcement, and that cost dominates. The view tag only skips the extra derivation for the \\~255/256 non-matches. &#x2A;*Measured end-to-end speedup: \\~2×.**"},"544":{"id":"faq-47","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#do-i-need-a-funded-account-to-receive-money","content":"For the `pool` method, **no** — you don't even need a Stellar account, since the contract authorizes withdrawals by signature. You do need *someone* to pay the Soroban fee: either your own fee-payer account, or a relayer fee-bump (which is the private option)."},"545":{"id":"faq-48","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#do-i-need-a-funded-account-to-receive-money","content":"For the `account` method the one-time account is created and funded by the **sender** (\\~1 XLM base reserve, or \\~1.5 XLM for tokens). You get the reserve back on a full `AccountMerge` sweep."},"546":{"id":"faq-49","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#can-i-claim-to-a-brand-new-empty-address","content":"For a token claim, yes — use a relayer **sponsored claim** (`--sponsored`), where the relayer fronts the reserves and the token is paid to your destination in the same transaction. For a pool withdraw, the destination must already exist as a Stellar account."},"547":{"id":"faq-50","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#is-my-keystore-encrypted","content":"**Yes, by default** (AES-256-GCM). You only get a plaintext keystore if you explicitly pass `--plaintext` / `--no-encrypt`."},"548":{"id":"faq-51","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#can-i-revoke-a-view-key-i-shared","content":"**No.** There is no revocation. Generate new keys and publish a new meta-address — and note that old payments stay visible to the old viewer."},"549":{"id":"faq-52","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#is-this-safe-for-mainnet","content":"**No.** The project has not had an external cryptographic audit. See Security."},"550":{"id":"faq-53","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#what-is-spp","content":"A reserved enum slot for a possible future integration with a separate, external private-payments effort. It is **not implemented** and not on Shade's roadmap — every call throws `MethodNotAvailableError`."},"551":{"id":"faq-54","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#methodrequirederror","content":"> A delivery method is required. Pass `opts.method: 'pool' | 'account' | 'auto'`."},"552":{"id":"faq-55","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#methodrequirederror","content":"There is deliberately no implicit default — the privacy trade-off must be a conscious choice. Pass `method` (CLI: `--method`). Use `'auto'` to let the client pick."},"553":{"id":"faq-56","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#contractidrequirederror","content":"The `pool` method is enabled but no contract id resolved. There is a built-in default only for `local`."},"554":{"id":"faq-57","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#contractidrequirederror","content":"**SDK:** pass `contractId: 'C...'` in `ClientConfig`."},"555":{"id":"faq-58","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#contractidrequirederror","content":"**CLI:** deploy the contract and write its id to `~/.stealth/<network>-contract`."},"556":{"id":"faq-59","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#methodnotenablederror","content":"The method isn't in `config.methods`. Add it: `methods: ['pool', 'account']`."},"557":{"id":"faq-60","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#methodnotavailableerror","content":"Either you asked for `spp` (never implemented), or you called the deprecated `withdraw()` without the `pool` method enabled."},"558":{"id":"faq-61","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#minimumamounterror","content":"An account-method XLM send must be **strictly greater than 1 XLM** — below that the new account can't meet its base reserve. Send more, or use `method: 'pool'`, which has no such floor."},"559":{"id":"faq-62","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#claimamounterror","content":"A partial account claim asked for more than the account can pay out while keeping &#x2A;*2× the base reserve (1.0 XLM)** and covering the fee. The error carries `.max` — retry within it, or do a full sweep (`merge: true` / drop `--no-merge`)."},"560":{"id":"faq-63","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#nobalanceerror","content":"The stealth address holds nothing in the pool **for that asset**. Either it was already withdrawn, or you're querying the wrong asset — pass the right `--asset` / `opts.asset`."},"561":{"id":"faq-64","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#announcementnotfounderror","content":"No announcement matching that stealth address was found for your keys. Causes:"},"562":{"id":"faq-65","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#announcementnotfounderror","content":"The payment isn't yours."},"563":{"id":"faq-66","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#announcementnotfounderror","content":"The deposit hasn't landed/indexed yet — wait and rescan."},"564":{"id":"faq-67","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#announcementnotfounderror","content":"(`balance`, `withdraw` and `scan` all page the full announcement set, so a high announcement index is *not* a cause.)"},"565":{"id":"faq-68","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#stealthaccountnotfounderror","content":"The stealth account isn't on Horizon yet — usually the funding send hasn't confirmed. Wait and retry."},"566":{"id":"faq-69","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#destinationtrustlineerror","content":"The destination doesn't (or can't yet) trust the asset you're claiming. &#x2A;*Add the trustline on the destination account before claiming.** If the destination doesn't exist at all, fund it first."},"567":{"id":"faq-70","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#feepayerrequirederror","content":"A pool withdraw needs an account to pay the Soroban fee, and none was supplied. Pass `feePayer` (CLI: `--fee-payer`, or better `$SHADE_FEE_PAYER`) — or route through a relayer with `--relay`."},"568":{"id":"faq-71","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#feepayeraddressrequirederror","content":"You set an external signer (`signTransaction`) on a pool claim but didn't pass `feePayerAddress&#x60;. With external signing the fee payer is identified by its **`G...` address**, never a secret. Pass `feePayerAddress`."},"569":{"id":"faq-72","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#sponsoredclaimmismatcherror","content":"**Take this seriously.** The relayer-prepared transaction does not match the operation list the SDK re-derived from your own inputs, so the SDK refused to sign. The message names the specific mismatch (a tampered payout destination, an extra appended operation, …). &#x2A;*The relayer may be malicious.** Don't retry blindly against the same relayer."},"570":{"id":"faq-73","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#entryarchivedrestoringerror","content":"Your pool `Balance`/`Nonce` entry archived (Soroban state expiration) and the automatic `RestoreFootprintOp` failed. **Your funds are safe** — the withdraw just can't proceed until the entry is restored. The message carries the underlying cause; common ones are an unfunded fee payer or a relayer rejection. Fix that and retry."},"571":{"id":"faq-74","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#entryarchivedrestoringerror","content":"Prevention: scan periodically. `get_balance`/`get_nonce` extend a live entry's TTL back to \\~1 year on read, so a passively scanning recipient never archives."},"572":{"id":"faq-75","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#transactionretryableerror","content":"The RPC returned a non-terminal status (e.g. `TRY_AGAIN_LATER`) — **nothing landed on-chain**. Safe to retry with a fresh submission. The error carries `.retryable`."},"573":{"id":"faq-76","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#wrongpassworderror--keystore-is-encrypted-but-no-password-provided","content":"Wrong or missing keystore/session password. The CLI prompts on stderr if you omit `--password`; the SDK session throws on an AES-GCM authentication failure."},"574":{"id":"faq-77","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#sessionintegrityerror","content":"The public key stored in the clear doesn't match the one re-derived from the decrypted private key — **the stored session may have been tampered with**. Don't trust the material; re-import your keys."},"575":{"id":"faq-78","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#invalidmetaaddress","content":"The meta-address failed prefix, length, hex, checksum, or on-curve/torsion validation. Check for a truncated or mistyped copy-paste."},"576":{"id":"faq-79","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#i-scanned-but-see-nothing","content":"Check `--network` matches where the payment was sent."},"577":{"id":"faq-80","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#i-scanned-but-see-nothing","content":"For the account method, the cursor is persisted — a previous scan may have advanced past it. Try `--full-rescan`."},"578":{"id":"faq-81","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#i-scanned-but-see-nothing","content":"Confirm the sender used *your* meta-address (the checksum makes a corrupted one throw, but a wrong-but-valid one won't)."},"579":{"id":"faq-82","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#i-scanned-but-see-nothing","content":"Confirm the deposit transaction actually landed."},"580":{"id":"faq-83","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#balance-shows-less-than-scan-found","content":"Expected in one case: `balance` suppresses fully-swept native accounts (live balance 0). For pool announcements the two commands can't diverge — `balance` reuses `scan`'s paged fetch and pages the full set."},"581":{"id":"faq-84","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#my-withdraw-signature-is-rejected-by-the-contract","content":"Almost always the raw-scalar footgun: you built a keypair from `recoverStealthPrivateKey`'s output via `Keypair.fromRawEd25519Seed()` (or similar), which hashes it into a *different* key. &#x2A;*Sign with `signWithStealthKey`.** See Core Concepts."},"582":{"id":"faq-85","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#my-withdraw-signature-is-rejected-by-the-contract","content":"Otherwise: check the contract id and network passphrase — the message binds both, so a signature built for one deployment/network is rejected on another."},"583":{"id":"faq-86","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#the-relayer-returns-402-insufficient_credit","content":"The relayer runs with `RELAYER_REQUIRE_CREDIT=1`. Top up via `POST /credit/claim` with the hash of an XLM payment to the relayer, and pass `fundingAccount` (CLI: `--funding-account`) on your requests."},"584":{"id":"faq-87","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#the-relayer-returns-401","content":"The proof-of-control challenge failed: an expired/unknown nonce (120-second TTL, single-use), an account mismatch, a signature that doesn't verify, or an `authAmount` that doesn't equal what the relayer will charge. On `/relay` the signature also binds the **inner-tx hash** and the network passphrase — a mismatch there fails too. Fetch a fresh nonce and re-sign."},"585":{"id":"faq-88","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#the-relayer-returns-429","content":"Rate limit: 10 requests/minute per client. Back off (`Retry-After` is set)."},"586":{"id":"faq-89","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#my-keys-dont-match-between-the-cli-and-the-sdk","content":"`appId` and `keyScope` must match across every tool. Defaults are `appId = 'default'`, `keyScope = 'stealth'` in both. Note `keyScope` is deliberately **decoupled from the network** — don't pass a network name into it."},"587":{"id":"faq-90","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#different-keys-every-time-i-derive-from-my-wallet","content":"Your signer is non-deterministic. Wallet-derived keys require an RFC 8032 deterministic signer; the SDK signs twice and throws when they differ, precisely to stop you from creating unrecoverable keys."},"588":{"id":"faq-91","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#next-steps","content":"Getting Started — install and first run"},"589":{"id":"faq-92","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#next-steps","content":"CLI Reference — every flag"},"590":{"id":"faq-93","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#next-steps","content":"SDK Reference — the full error table"},"591":{"id":"faq-94","page_id":"faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#next-steps","content":"Security — limits and assumptions"},"592":{"id":"getting-started","page_id":"getting-started","type":"page","content":"Getting Started","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Build"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started"},"593":{"id":"getting-started-0","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started","content":"Run Shade end-to-end on a local Stellar network: prerequisites, install, the one-command demo, deploying the Soroban contract, and your first commands."},"594":{"id":"getting-started-1","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#prerequisites","content":"Prerequisites"},"595":{"id":"getting-started-2","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#install","content":"Install"},"596":{"id":"getting-started-3","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#deploying-the-contract","content":"Deploying the contract"},"597":{"id":"getting-started-4","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#your-first-commands","content":"Your first commands"},"598":{"id":"getting-started-5","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#running-the-relayer-optional","content":"Running the relayer (optional)"},"599":{"id":"getting-started-6","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#using-the-sdk-instead","content":"Using the SDK instead"},"600":{"id":"getting-started-7","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#running-from-source","content":"Running from source"},"601":{"id":"getting-started-8","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"The fastest path: run the demo"},"602":{"id":"getting-started-9","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#deploying-to-the-local-network","content":"Deploying to the local network"},"603":{"id":"getting-started-10","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#tests","content":"Tests"},"604":{"id":"getting-started-11","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"Networks"},"605":{"id":"getting-started-12","page_id":"getting-started","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"606":{"id":"getting-started-13","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started","content":"\\{/\\* adapted from shade\\@36217c4 docs/05-getting-started.md \\*/}"},"607":{"id":"getting-started-14","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started","content":"import \\{ Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout';"},"608":{"id":"getting-started-15","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started","content":"Install Shade and make your first stealth payment in a few minutes. This page covers prerequisites, install, deploying the contract, your first real commands, and the from-source demo