[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#deploying-the-contract","content":"*(local only)* a built-in default"},"619":{"id":"getting-started-26","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#deploying-the-contract","content":"There is deliberately **no built-in testnet address** — testnet resets periodically, and a stale placeholder would only produce an opaque Soroban failure later. For testnet you must deploy and save the id yourself. Building the contract Wasm requires a checkout of the repo (see Running from source):"},"620":{"id":"getting-started-27","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#deploying-the-contract","content":"If you skip this, the CLI throws an actionable error naming the exact file to write, and the SDK throws `ContractIdRequiredError`."},"621":{"id":"getting-started-28","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#your-first-commands","content":"The examples below use `--network local` (the Docker network from Running from source); substitute `--network testnet` once you've deployed a contract there."},"622":{"id":"getting-started-29","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#running-the-relayer-optional","content":"The relayer pays your withdrawal fee so you never reveal a funded account of your own. It isn't published to npm — run it from a checkout of the repo:"},"623":{"id":"getting-started-30","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#running-the-relayer-optional","content":"Then pass `--relay http://localhost:3000` to `claim`/`withdraw`. See Relayer for endpoints, credit gating, and deployment."},"624":{"id":"getting-started-31","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#using-the-sdk-instead","content":"Full API in the SDK Reference."},"625":{"id":"getting-started-32","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#running-from-source","content":"Everything above uses the published npm packages. Clone and build the repo when you want to run the local Stellar network, build and deploy the contract, or run the end-to-end demo:"},"626":{"id":"getting-started-33","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#running-from-source","content":"The local network is the `stellar/quickstart:testing` image run with `--local`, exposed on port `8000`."},"627":{"id":"getting-started-34","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"The demo takes roughly 3 minutes and exercises the whole system:"},"628":{"id":"getting-started-35","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"Deploys the stealth pool contract + the native XLM SAC"},"629":{"id":"getting-started-36","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"Starts the relayer service"},"630":{"id":"getting-started-37","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"Generates stealth meta-addresses for Bob"},"631":{"id":"getting-started-38","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"Alice deposits 100 XLM into the pool"},"632":{"id":"getting-started-39","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"Alice deposits 200 USDC into the pool (multi-token)"},"633":{"id":"getting-started-40","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"Bob scans and detects both deposits with his view key"},"634":{"id":"getting-started-41","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"Bob withdraws XLM directly (a fee-payer pays the Soroban fee)"},"635":{"id":"getting-started-42","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"Bob withdraws USDC via the relayer (fee-bump for privacy)"},"636":{"id":"getting-started-43","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#the-fastest-path-run-the-demo","content":"Verifies there is no on-chain link between Bob and the stealth addresses"},"637":{"id":"getting-started-44","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#deploying-to-the-local-network","content":"The script builds the contract, deploys it, and writes the resulting contract id where the CLI will find it."},"638":{"id":"getting-started-45","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"Network"},"639":{"id":"getting-started-46","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"Passphrase"},"640":{"id":"getting-started-47","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"RPC"},"641":{"id":"getting-started-48","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"Horizon"},"642":{"id":"getting-started-49","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"`local`"},"643":{"id":"getting-started-50","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"Standalone"},"644":{"id":"getting-started-51","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"`http://localhost:8000/soroban/rpc`"},"645":{"id":"getting-started-52","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"`http://localhost:8000`"},"646":{"id":"getting-started-53","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"`testnet`"},"647":{"id":"getting-started-54","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"Testnet"},"648":{"id":"getting-started-55","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"`https://soroban-testnet.stellar.org`"},"649":{"id":"getting-started-56","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"`https://horizon-testnet.stellar.org`"},"650":{"id":"getting-started-57","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#networks","content":"Fund a `local` or `testnet` account with friendbot before using it."},"651":{"id":"getting-started-58","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#next-steps","content":"CLI Reference — every command and flag"},"652":{"id":"getting-started-59","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#next-steps","content":"SDK Reference — `StealthClient`, types, errors"},"653":{"id":"getting-started-60","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#next-steps","content":"Delivery Methods — choosing `pool` vs `account`"},"654":{"id":"getting-started-61","page_id":"getting-started","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started#next-steps","content":"FAQ & Troubleshooting — when something fails"},"655":{"id":"index","page_id":"index","type":"page","content":"Introduction","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Learn"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs"},"656":{"id":"index-0","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"Shade gives every Stellar payment its own fresh, unlinkable stealth address. Publish one public handle; nobody watching the chain can tell those payments are yours."},"657":{"id":"index-1","page_id":"index","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs#the-problem-your-address-is-a-glass-mailbox","content":"The problem: your address is a glass mailbox"},"658":{"id":"index-2","page_id":"index","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"What Shade does — and does not — hide"},"659":{"id":"index-3","page_id":"index","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs#why-stellar-needed-a-different-design","content":"Why Stellar needed a different design"},"660":{"id":"index-4","page_id":"index","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs#who-this-is-for","content":"Who this is for"},"661":{"id":"index-5","page_id":"index","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs#whats-implemented-today","content":"What's implemented today"},"662":{"id":"index-6","page_id":"index","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs#status-pre-audit-not-for-mainnet","content":"Status: pre-audit, not for mainnet"},"663":{"id":"index-7","page_id":"index","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"664":{"id":"index-8","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"\\{/\\* adapted from shade\\@36217c4 docs/01-introduction.md \\*/}"},"665":{"id":"index-9","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"import \\{ Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout';"},"666":{"id":"index-10","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"Shade gives every payment its own fresh, unlinkable address on Stellar. You publish **one** public handle; anyone can pay you, but nobody watching the chain can tell those payments are yours — or that they're related to each other."},"667":{"id":"index-11","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"This page explains what Shade is, the problem it solves, and who it's for. If you want to start using it, jump to Getting Started."},"668":{"id":"index-12","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"**Get Shade from npm:**"},"669":{"id":"index-13","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"Prefer to see it run end-to-end first? The repository ships a from-source demo (needs Node.js 20+, Docker, Stellar CLI and a Rust toolchain — it deploys the contract, runs a relayer, and walks a full send → scan → claim cycle on a local network):"},"670":{"id":"index-14","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"Full setup in Getting Started."},"671":{"id":"index-15","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#the-problem-your-address-is-a-glass-mailbox","content":"On a normal blockchain, your address is public and permanent. Every payment to it is visible and tied to you forever. Reuse it and the whole world sees your balance and your history."},"672":{"id":"index-16","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#the-problem-your-address-is-a-glass-mailbox","content":"Shade gives you a **new mailbox for every single payment** — and only *you* can tell which mailboxes are yours. You hand out one public **meta-address**; senders use it to compute a brand-new one-time address each time. On-chain, those addresses look unrelated to you and to each other."},"673":{"id":"index-17","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"This distinction is the single most important thing to understand:"},"674":{"id":"index-18","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"Three terms first, so the table below reads cleanly. Full definitions are in Core Concepts:"},"675":{"id":"index-19","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"**Stealth address** — the fresh one-time address a sender computes from your meta-address. On-chain it looks like any ordinary Stellar address."},"676":{"id":"index-20","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"**View key** — one half of your identity. It can **find** payments sent to you, but **cannot spend** them. Safe to delegate; the other half, the **spend key**, moves the money and never leaves you."},"677":{"id":"index-21","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"**Relayer** — an optional helper service that pays a transaction fee on your behalf, so claiming your money doesn't reveal a wallet of your own. See Relayer."},"678":{"id":"index-22","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"**Hides**"},"679":{"id":"index-23","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"*Who* the recipient is. A stealth address is unlinkable to your meta-address without your view key."},"680":{"id":"index-24","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"**Hides**"},"681":{"id":"index-25","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"Which funded accounts you control — a relayer can pay the transaction fee so your own wallet never appears."},"682":{"id":"index-26","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"**Does NOT hide**"},"683":{"id":"index-27","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"That *a* payment happened, or its amount."},"684":{"id":"index-28","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"**Does NOT hide**"},"685":{"id":"index-29","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"The flow of funds. Shade is **not a mixer**: a pool deposit and its withdrawal both name the same stealth key on-chain."},"686":{"id":"index-30","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"**Does NOT hide**"},"687":{"id":"index-31","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"Timing correlation. Withdraw right after a deposit and the link is obvious."},"688":{"id":"index-32","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-shade-does--and-does-not--hide","content":"**Privacy here is about identity, not invisibility.** The cryptography gives you the tools; behaviour (timing, amount patterns, address reuse) can still deanonymize you."},"689":{"id":"index-33","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why-stellar-needed-a-different-design","content":"Stellar charges a &#x2A;*minimum balance reserve (MBR)** of \\~1 XLM for every account that exists. A naive stealth-address implementation creates one account per payment and locks \\~1 XLM in each. On chains where accounts are free or negligible, that's fine; on Stellar it makes per-payment accounts impractical."},"690":{"id":"index-34","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why-stellar-needed-a-different-design","content":"Shade's answer is a **Soroban pool contract** that holds funds with per-stealth-key accounting, so no new account is created per payment. The cost drops from \\~1 XLM of locked reserve to a Soroban invocation fee (on the order of \\~0.01 XLM)."},"691":{"id":"index-35","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#who-this-is-for","content":"**People receiving payments** who don't want a public, permanent link between their identity and every incoming transfer — freelancers, donation recipients, anyone publishing a payment handle."},"692":{"id":"index-36","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#who-this-is-for","content":"**Application developers** who want stealth payments without implementing elliptic-curve math or hand-building Soroban transactions. See the SDK Reference."},"693":{"id":"index-37","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#who-this-is-for","content":"**Wallet and tooling builders** who want the primitives only. `@shade/crypto` is pure TypeScript with **zero** `@stellar/stellar-sdk` dependency."},"694":{"id":"index-38","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#whats-implemented-today","content":"Two delivery methods — &#x2A;*`pool`** (Soroban contract; works with any **SAC** token, i.e. any asset exposed to Soroban via a *Stellar Asset Contract&#x2A; — native XLM, USDC, anything issued) and &#x2A;*`account`** (a direct one-time Stellar account, or a *claimable balance* — a pending transfer the recipient later claims). See Delivery Methods."},"695":{"id":"index-39","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#whats-implemented-today","content":"A **relayer** for fee-bumping and reserve-fronting. See Relayer."},"696":{"id":"index-40","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#whats-implemented-today","content":"External signing via **Freighter** (the Stellar browser wallet), encrypted browser sessions, and wallet-signature key derivation."},"697":{"id":"index-41","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#whats-implemented-today","content":"A reference **CLI** (`shade`) and a **TypeScript SDK**."},"698":{"id":"index-42","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#status-pre-audit-not-for-mainnet","content":"The protocol and this implementation have **not undergone an external cryptographic audit**. Treat the project as production-track but pre-audit, and do not put mainnet value at risk. Read Security before going further."},"699":{"id":"index-43","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#next-steps","content":"Core Concepts — DKSAP (the Dual-Key Stealth Address Protocol Shade is built on), view/spend keys, meta-addresses, view tags"},"700":{"id":"index-44","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#next-steps","content":"Architecture — the components and how data flows between them"},"701":{"id":"index-45","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#next-steps","content":"Getting Started — run it locally"},"702":{"id":"index-46","page_id":"index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#next-steps","content":"Security — threat model, assumptions, and limits"},"703":{"id":"relayer","page_id":"relayer","type":"page","content":"Relayer","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Build"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer"},"704":{"id":"relayer-0","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer","content":"The Shade relayer: fee-bumping, sponsored claims and the credit system — endpoints, proof-of-control auth, configuration and operational warnings."},"705":{"id":"relayer-1","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#what-it-solves","content":"What it solves"},"706":{"id":"relayer-2","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Endpoints"},"707":{"id":"relayer-3","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"`POST /relay`"},"708":{"id":"relayer-4","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor","content":"`POST /sponsor`"},"709":{"id":"relayer-5","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor-claimprepare-and-submit","content":"`POST /sponsor-claim/prepare` and `/submit`"},"710":{"id":"relayer-6","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#the-credit-system","content":"The credit system"},"711":{"id":"relayer-7","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#proof-of-control","content":"Proof of control"},"712":{"id":"relayer-8","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#the-ledger","content":"The ledger"},"713":{"id":"relayer-9","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#rate-limiting","content":"Rate limiting"},"714":{"id":"relayer-10","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Configuration"},"715":{"id":"relayer-11","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#running-it","content":"Running it"},"716":{"id":"relayer-12","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#railway-testnet","content":"Railway (testnet)"},"717":{"id":"relayer-13","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#operational-warnings","content":"Operational warnings"},"718":{"id":"relayer-14","page_id":"relayer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/relayer#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"719":{"id":"relayer-15","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer","content":"\\{/\\* adapted from shade\\@36217c4 docs/08-relayer.md \\*/}"},"720":{"id":"relayer-16","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer","content":"import \\{ Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout';"},"721":{"id":"relayer-17","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer","content":"The relayer is the reference service (`packages/relayer`) that an app or community runs. It solves a chicken-and-egg problem: to claim your money you'd normally need a funded Stellar account to pay the fee — but *using* a funded account links it to you, undoing the privacy."},"722":{"id":"relayer-18","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer","content":"This page covers what it does, its endpoints, the credit system, configuration, and deployment."},"723":{"id":"relayer-19","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#what-it-solves","content":"**Fee-bump** (`/relay`) — the relayer pays your withdrawal's fee, so you never reveal a funded account of your own. This is purely about **privacy**: the relayer sees the transaction envelope but learns nothing about your other accounts."},"724":{"id":"relayer-20","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#what-it-solves","content":"**Reserve fronting / sponsored claims** (`/sponsor`, `/sponsor-claim/*`) — it fronts the \\~1 XLM account reserve (plus \\~0.5 XLM trustline reserve for tokens) so you can cash out to a **fresh, unfunded address**."},"725":{"id":"relayer-21","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Endpoint"},"726":{"id":"relayer-22","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"What it does"},"727":{"id":"relayer-23","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"`GET /health`"},"728":{"id":"relayer-24","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Status, network, relayer address, balance, `requireCredit`"},"729":{"id":"relayer-25","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"`POST /relay`"},"730":{"id":"relayer-26","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Fee-bump and submit a signed transaction"},"731":{"id":"relayer-27","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"`POST /sponsor`"},"732":{"id":"relayer-28","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Create a stealth account (funded `CreateAccount` from the relayer)"},"733":{"id":"relayer-29","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"`POST /sponsor-claim/prepare`"},"734":{"id":"relayer-30","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Build an unsigned sponsored-claim transaction"},"735":{"id":"relayer-31","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"`POST /sponsor-claim/submit`"},"736":{"id":"relayer-32","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Co-sign + submit a sponsored claim"},"737":{"id":"relayer-33","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"`POST /credit/claim`"},"738":{"id":"relayer-34","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Top up credit by proving an XLM payment via `txHash`"},"739":{"id":"relayer-35","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"`GET /credit/challenge`"},"740":{"id":"relayer-36","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Issue a proof-of-control nonce"},"741":{"id":"relayer-37","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"`GET /credit/:account`"},"742":{"id":"relayer-38","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#endpoints","content":"Read a credit balance"},"743":{"id":"relayer-39","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"Body: `{ xdr, fundingAccount?, nonce?, signature? }` → `{ txHash, success: true }`"},"744":{"id":"relayer-40","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"Wraps your signed inner transaction in a fee-bump and submits it. Abuse guards apply on **every** path, credit-gated or not:"},"745":{"id":"relayer-41","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"Guard"},"746":{"id":"relayer-42","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"Default"},"747":{"id":"relayer-43","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"Max operations in the inner tx"},"748":{"id":"relayer-44","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"5 (`MAX_RELAY_OPS`)"},"749":{"id":"relayer-45","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"Timebounds must be present, unexpired, and bounded"},"750":{"id":"relayer-46","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"≤ now + 600s (`MAX_RELAY_TIMEBOUNDS_SECONDS`)"},"751":{"id":"relayer-47","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"Memos"},"752":{"id":"relayer-48","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"**Forbidden** — a relayed withdrawal has no legitimate memo, and one could leak or tag metadata"},"753":{"id":"relayer-49","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"Fetched base fee clamp"},"754":{"id":"relayer-50","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"10,000 stroops (`MAX_BASE_FEE`)"},"755":{"id":"relayer-51","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"Absolute outer fee cap"},"756":{"id":"relayer-52","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-relay","content":"0.1 XLM (`MAX_RELAY_FEE_XLM`)"},"757":{"id":"relayer-53","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor","content":"Body: `{ address, startingBalance?, fundingAccount, nonce, signature }` → `{ txHash, stealthAddress }`"},"758":{"id":"relayer-54","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor","content":"Creates a stealth account with a plain funded `CreateAccount`. &#x2A;*Fail-closed by design:** this route *always* requires an authenticated funding account and *always* debits `startingBalance + fee` from its credit, regardless of `RELAYER_REQUIRE_CREDIT` — so it can never be used as a free XLM faucet. `startingBalance` is capped at `SPONSOR_MAX_XLM` (default 5)."},"759":{"id":"relayer-55","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor","content":"There is deliberately **no sponsorship sandwich** here: `EndSponsoringFutureReserves` must be signed by the sponsored account, whose key nobody holds at creation time. The sandwich lives only in `/sponsor-claim`, where the client holds the stealth key and co-signs."},"760":{"id":"relayer-56","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor-claimprepare-and-submit","content":"**prepare** — body `{ stealthAddress, asset, balanceId, destination, amount }` → `{ xdr, expiresAt }`"},"761":{"id":"relayer-57","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor-claimprepare-and-submit","content":"Builds a relayer-sourced, **unsigned** transaction (60-second timebounds) with this exact operation sequence:"},"762":{"id":"relayer-58","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor-claimprepare-and-submit","content":"The payout rides in the same transaction because a stealth account created with `startingBalance: '0'` under sponsorship can never pay a fee to move the tokens itself. It also verifies up front that the destination exists and already trusts the asset."},"763":{"id":"relayer-59","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor-claimprepare-and-submit","content":"**submit** — body `{ xdr, stealthAddress, asset, balanceId, destination, amount, fundingAccount?, nonce?, signature? }` → `{ txHash }`"},"764":{"id":"relayer-60","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#post-sponsor-claimprepare-and-submit","content":"The client attaches its stealth signature and returns the XDR. The relayer then rebuilds the expected operation list from the **trusted inputs** and compares field-by-field (type, per-op source, destination, asset, amount, balanceId, sponsoredId) before adding its own signature. A client cannot mutate any operation and still pass. It also enforces a per-op fee cap (200 stroops/op), the advertised 60-second TTL, and a no-memo rule."},"765":{"id":"relayer-61","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-credit-system","content":"The relayer is metered so it isn't a free-for-all:"},"766":{"id":"relayer-62","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-credit-system","content":"An app sends the relayer a normal XLM payment."},"767":{"id":"relayer-63","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-credit-system","content":"It calls `POST /credit/claim` with the **transaction hash**."},"768":{"id":"relayer-64","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-credit-system","content":"The relayer checks Horizon: the transaction succeeded, is sourced by that funding account, contains native payment ops **to the relayer** whose op-source is the funding account, and hasn't already been claimed. It sums every qualifying payment op and credits that amount."},"769":{"id":"relayer-65","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-credit-system","content":"From then on the relayer serves that app's requests, drawing the credit down."},"770":{"id":"relayer-66","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-credit-system","content":"Credit gating is **on by default on non-local networks** (testnet/mainnet) and off on `local&#x60; for development. Set &#x2A;*`RELAYER_REQUIRE_CREDIT=0` or `=1`** to override the default explicitly."},"771":{"id":"relayer-67","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#proof-of-control","content":"Fee-spending requests are authenticated by an **ed25519 challenge/response** (not an API key or HMAC):"},"772":{"id":"relayer-68","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#proof-of-control","content":"`GET /credit/challenge?account=G...` returns a fresh random 32-byte nonce (120-second TTL, single-use, in-memory)."},"773":{"id":"relayer-69","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#proof-of-control","content":"The client signs the canonical message with the funding account's key:"},"774":{"id":"relayer-70","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#proof-of-control","content":"The relayer verifies the signature, then **consumes** the nonce."},"775":{"id":"relayer-71","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#proof-of-control","content":"The signed message binds the endpoint, the account, the nonce, and the exact **amount** authorized. On `/relay`, `bind` is additionally the **inner transaction hash**, so an intercepted `{nonce, signature}` cannot be paired with a different inner XDR of the same fee."},"776":{"id":"relayer-72","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-ledger","content":"A durable JSON file (default `./data/credit-ledger.json`, override with `CREDIT_LEDGER_PATH`):"},"777":{"id":"relayer-73","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-ledger","content":"All arithmetic on **BigInt stroops** — never floats."},"778":{"id":"relayer-74","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-ledger","content":"**Atomic writes** (write-tmp + rename), so a crash mid-write can't corrupt it."},"779":{"id":"relayer-75","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-ledger","content":"**Per-account async locks**, so two concurrent reservations against a balance that only covers one cannot both succeed."},"780":{"id":"relayer-76","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-ledger","content":"**Reserve → settle / refund** around each submit: the fee is debited *before* submission, settled on success, refunded if the submit throws. Reservations carry a unique id and a terminal state (`OUTSTANDING` / `SETTLED` / `REFUNDED`) so a replay can't refund a legitimate charge."},"781":{"id":"relayer-77","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-ledger","content":"**Idempotent by ref** via O(1) net counters (debits minus refunds), so a duplicate is a no-op while a genuine retry after a refund still re-debits."},"782":{"id":"relayer-78","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-ledger","content":"Consumed deposit tx hashes make credit claims idempotent."},"783":{"id":"relayer-79","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#the-ledger","content":"Sponsored reserves are tracked in `sponsoredHeld` under a per-funder ceiling (`SPONSOR_CLAIM_MAX_HELD`)."},"784":{"id":"relayer-80","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#rate-limiting","content":"A token bucket: **10 requests/minute per client**, `429` with `Retry-After` when empty."},"785":{"id":"relayer-81","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#rate-limiting","content":"Client identity comes from the direct IP by default. `X-Forwarded-For` is only trusted when you explicitly declare proxies via `TRUST_PROXY_HOPS`, and even then hops are counted **from the right** — the entries your own infrastructure appended — so a client cannot forge extra left-hand entries to mint a fresh bucket per request."},"786":{"id":"relayer-82","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Variable"},"787":{"id":"relayer-83","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Default"},"788":{"id":"relayer-84","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Purpose"},"789":{"id":"relayer-85","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`RELAYER_SECRET`"},"790":{"id":"relayer-86","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"—"},"791":{"id":"relayer-87","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Relayer secret key. Unset on `local` → a random keypair is generated (dev only); **unset on a non-local network now fails fast** (a random unfunded key can't pay fees)."},"792":{"id":"relayer-88","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`NETWORK`"},"793":{"id":"relayer-89","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`local`"},"794":{"id":"relayer-90","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`local` → standalone + `localhost:8000`; otherwise testnet"},"795":{"id":"relayer-91","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`PORT`"},"796":{"id":"relayer-92","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`3000`"},"797":{"id":"relayer-93","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Listen port"},"798":{"id":"relayer-94","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`RELAYER_REQUIRE_CREDIT`"},"799":{"id":"relayer-95","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"non-local: `1`, local: `0`"},"800":{"id":"relayer-96","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Require prepaid credit for `/relay` and `/sponsor-claim/submit`. Defaults **on** for testnet/mainnet, **off** for local; set `0`/`1` to override."},"801":{"id":"relayer-97","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`CREDIT_LEDGER_PATH`"},"802":{"id":"relayer-98","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`./data/credit-ledger.json`"},"803":{"id":"relayer-99","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Ledger file path. **On a non-local network, point this at a mounted persistent volume** — the default is ephemeral on Railway (see warning below)."},"804":{"id":"relayer-100","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`TRUST_PROXY_HOPS`"},"805":{"id":"relayer-101","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`0`"},"806":{"id":"relayer-102","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Trusted reverse-proxy hops, counted from the right"},"807":{"id":"relayer-103","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`TRUST_PROXY`"},"808":{"id":"relayer-104","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"—"},"809":{"id":"relayer-105","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Legacy: `true` → 1 hop"},"810":{"id":"relayer-106","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`SPONSOR_MAX_XLM`"},"811":{"id":"relayer-107","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`5`"},"812":{"id":"relayer-108","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Cap on `/sponsor` starting balance"},"813":{"id":"relayer-109","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`SPONSOR_CLAIM_MAX_HELD`"},"814":{"id":"relayer-110","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`10`"},"815":{"id":"relayer-111","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Per-funder sponsored-reserve ceiling"},"816":{"id":"relayer-112","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`MAX_RELAY_OPS`"},"817":{"id":"relayer-113","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`5`"},"818":{"id":"relayer-114","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Max ops in a relayed inner tx"},"819":{"id":"relayer-115","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`MAX_BASE_FEE`"},"820":{"id":"relayer-116","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`10000`"},"821":{"id":"relayer-117","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Clamp on the fetched base fee (stroops)"},"822":{"id":"relayer-118","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`MAX_RELAY_FEE_XLM`"},"823":{"id":"relayer-119","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`0.1`"},"824":{"id":"relayer-120","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Absolute outer fee cap"},"825":{"id":"relayer-121","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`MAX_RELAY_TIMEBOUNDS_SECONDS`"},"826":{"id":"relayer-122","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`600`"},"827":{"id":"relayer-123","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Max future window for the inner tx `maxTime`"},"828":{"id":"relayer-124","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`CORS_ORIGIN`"},"829":{"id":"relayer-125","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`*`"},"830":{"id":"relayer-126","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Allowed origin"},"831":{"id":"relayer-127","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"`DEBUG`"},"832":{"id":"relayer-128","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"—"},"833":{"id":"relayer-129","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#configuration","content":"Enable debug logs"},"834":{"id":"relayer-130","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#running-it","content":"The relayer is deployed from a clone of the Shade repository:"},"835":{"id":"relayer-131","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#railway-testnet","content":"The relayer ships ready for Railway (`packages/relayer/railway.json`: NIXPACKS build, `npm run start` → `node dist/index.js`, health check on `/health`)."},"836":{"id":"relayer-132","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#railway-testnet","content":"Fund a testnet account via friendbot"},"837":{"id":"relayer-133","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#railway-testnet","content":"Set `RELAYER_SECRET` to its secret and `NETWORK=testnet`"},"838":{"id":"relayer-134","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#railway-testnet","content":"Point Railway's root at `packages/relayer`"},"839":{"id":"relayer-135","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#railway-testnet","content":"Deploy and hit `/health`"},"840":{"id":"relayer-136","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#railway-testnet","content":"Step-by-step lives in `packages/relayer/README.md`."},"841":{"id":"relayer-137","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#operational-warnings","content":"Read these before running a relayer with real value:"},"842":{"id":"relayer-138","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#operational-warnings","content":"**Authentication is on by default on non-local networks.** `/relay` and `/sponsor-claim/submit` require credit whenever `RELAYER_REQUIRE_CREDIT` is unset on testnet/mainnet (it defaults on); on `local` it defaults off for development. If you explicitly set `RELAYER_REQUIRE_CREDIT=0` on a funded deployment, those endpoints perform **no authentication** — anyone can make the relayer pay fees (and front \\~1 XLM reserves) for any conforming transaction, bounded only by an in-memory per-IP rate limit, which across many IPs is a hot-wallet drain vector. &#x2A;*Do not disable credit on a deployment that holds meaningful funds.** (`/sponsor` is fail-closed and always authenticated.)"},"843":{"id":"relayer-139","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#operational-warnings","content":"**The ledger file is not durable on ephemeral filesystems.** On Railway, a redeploy or restart wipes credit balances *and* the consumed-tx records — meaning a previously claimed deposit could be re-claimed afterwards. The relayer now **warns loudly at startup** when credit is enabled on a non-local network and `CREDIT_LEDGER_PATH` looks ephemeral (unset or under `./data`); point it at a mounted persistent volume. A durable external store (Postgres/Redis) is the full production fix and is on the roadmap."},"844":{"id":"relayer-140","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#operational-warnings","content":"**Challenge nonces and rate-limit buckets are in-memory and single-node.** Horizontal scaling breaks both the rate limit and the single-use nonce guarantee; a restart invalidates all outstanding nonces."},"845":{"id":"relayer-141","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#operational-warnings","content":"**`/sponsor-claim/prepare` is unauthenticated** and performs 2–3 Horizon lookups per call — a cheap amplification surface, protected only by the rate limit."},"846":{"id":"relayer-142","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#operational-warnings","content":"**`CORS_ORIGIN` defaults to `*`** (the relayer now warns at startup when it is `*` on a non-local network — set it to your app origin). An unset `RELAYER_SECRET` now **fails fast on non-local networks** instead of silently booting an unfunded random keypair (a random key is still allowed on `local`)."},"847":{"id":"relayer-143","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#next-steps","content":"Delivery Methods — when a claim needs the relayer"},"848":{"id":"relayer-144","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#next-steps","content":"SDK Reference — the typed `RelayerClient`"},"849":{"id":"relayer-145","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#next-steps","content":"Security — the relayer's place in the threat model"},"850":{"id":"relayer-146","page_id":"relayer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/relayer#next-steps","content":"FAQ & Troubleshooting — relayer errors"},"851":{"id":"sdk","page_id":"sdk","type":"page","content":"SDK Reference","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Build"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk"},"852":{"id":"sdk-0","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk","content":"The @shade/sdk and @shade/crypto API: StealthClient, types, typed errors, Freighter signing, encrypted sessions and the stealth-address primitives."},"853":{"id":"sdk-1","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#quick-start","content":"Quick start"},"854":{"id":"sdk-2","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#stealthclient","content":"`StealthClient`"},"855":{"id":"sdk-3","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#constructor","content":"Constructor"},"856":{"id":"sdk-4","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#static-methods","content":"Static methods"},"857":{"id":"sdk-5","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#send","content":"`send`"},"858":{"id":"sdk-6","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#scan--scanwithcursor","content":"`scan` / `scanWithCursor`"},"859":{"id":"sdk-7","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#balance","content":"`balance`"},"860":{"id":"sdk-8","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#claim","content":"`claim`"},"861":{"id":"sdk-9","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#withdraw--deprecated","content":"`withdraw` — deprecated"},"862":{"id":"sdk-10","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#types-shadesdk","content":"Types (`@shade/sdk`)"},"863":{"id":"sdk-11","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#sendopts","content":"`SendOpts`"},"864":{"id":"sdk-12","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#claimopts","content":"`ClaimOpts`"},"865":{"id":"sdk-13","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#external-signing-freighter","content":"External signing (Freighter)"},"866":{"id":"sdk-14","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#wallet-derived-keys","content":"Wallet-derived keys"},"867":{"id":"sdk-15","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#sessions-stealthsession","content":"Sessions (`StealthSession`)"},"868":{"id":"sdk-16","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"`RelayerClient`"},"869":{"id":"sdk-17","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#typed-errors","content":"Typed errors"},"870":{"id":"sdk-18","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#helpers","content":"Helpers"},"871":{"id":"sdk-19","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#shadecrypto","content":"`@shade/crypto`"},"872":{"id":"sdk-20","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#types","content":"Types"},"873":{"id":"sdk-21","page_id":"sdk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/sdk#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"874":{"id":"sdk-22","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk","content":"\\{/\\* adapted from shade\\@36217c4 docs/07-sdk-reference.md \\*/}"},"875":{"id":"sdk-23","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk","content":"import \\{ Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout';"},"876":{"id":"sdk-24","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk","content":"Two packages ship on npm for application developers:"},"877":{"id":"sdk-25","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk","content":"**`@shade/crypto`** — pure stealth-address math (keys, scanning, recovery, HD/mnemonic). **Zero** Stellar dependency; usable anywhere."},"878":{"id":"sdk-26","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk","content":"**`@shade/sdk`** — the batteries-included client. Wraps all Horizon/Soroban I/O behind `StealthClient`, so you never touch DKSAP math or transaction XDR."},"879":{"id":"sdk-27","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk","content":"Install with `npm install @shade/sdk`, or `npm install @shade/crypto` alone for just the primitives. Every symbol on this page is exported from the package named in its heading."},"880":{"id":"sdk-28","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#constructor","content":"Throws &#x2A;*`ContractIdRequiredError`** if `'pool'` is enabled and no contract id resolves — failing loudly here instead of surfacing an opaque Soroban error on the first pool call."},"881":{"id":"sdk-29","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#static-methods","content":"Both are offline — no network needed. `fromMnemonic()` generates a phrase when called with no argument and returns it alongside the keys for backup."},"882":{"id":"sdk-30","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#send","content":"A method is **required** on every call. Throws `MethodRequiredError` if `opts.method` is missing, `MethodNotEnabledError` if the resolved method isn't in `config.methods`."},"883":{"id":"sdk-31","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#send","content":"With an external signer, pass the sender's **public** `G...` address in the `senderSecret` position."},"884":{"id":"sdk-32","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#scan--scanwithcursor","content":"`scan` is the simple form. `scanWithCursor` returns an updated per-method cursor to persist and pass to the next call for incremental discovery."},"885":{"id":"sdk-33","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#balance","content":"Like a scan, but suppresses fully-swept/merged native accounts (live balance 0) so a spent stealth account is never reported as spendable."},"886":{"id":"sdk-34","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#claim","content":"Takes a `Payment` returned from `scan` and branches on its `method`: `'pool'` → signed withdraw; `'account'` → sweep / partial payout / sponsored claim."},"887":{"id":"sdk-35","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#external-signing-freighter","content":"A web app should **never** hold a raw secret. Pass a signer function instead:"},"888":{"id":"sdk-36","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#external-signing-freighter","content":"**The security boundary:** the signer only ever applies to the **sender** and **fee-payer** legs — the ordinary Stellar signatures. The **stealth-key** legs always sign locally inside the SDK, because a wallet cannot hold a key it never generated. &#x2A;Your wallet never touches the stealth scalar.*"},"889":{"id":"sdk-37","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#external-signing-freighter","content":"On a pool claim with a signer you must also pass `feePayerAddress` (the fee payer's `G...`), or you get `FeePayerAddressRequiredError` — this prevents the SDK from ever calling `Keypair.fromSecret` on a public key."},"890":{"id":"sdk-38","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#wallet-derived-keys","content":"Determinism is verified **by default**: a randomized or non-canonical signer would derive different (unrecoverable) keys on every call, so it fails loudly instead. Pass `verifyDeterminism: false` only for a signer you know is RFC 8032 deterministic."},"891":{"id":"sdk-39","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#wallet-derived-keys","content":"`keyScope` / `appId` must **match across every tool** deriving from the same wallet. The defaults line up with the CLI's `--key-scope` / `--app-id`."},"892":{"id":"sdk-40","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#sessions-stealthsession","content":"Cookie-free browser sessions over any key/value store:"},"893":{"id":"sdk-41","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#sessions-stealthsession","content":"Methods: `saveKeys`, `unlock`, `lock`, `hasKeys`, `clear`, `loadScanState`, `saveScanState`; getter `keys`."},"894":{"id":"sdk-42","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#sessions-stealthsession","content":"**Crypto:** PBKDF2-SHA256 (600,000 iterations) → AES-256-GCM, via `globalThis.crypto.subtle` only (browsers and Node 18+). Public keys are stored in the clear; private keys and scan state are encrypted. This is intentionally separate from the CLI keystore (which uses Node's scrypt)."},"895":{"id":"sdk-43","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#sessions-stealthsession","content":"**Integrity:** on `unlock`, both public keys are re-derived from the decrypted private scalars and compared to the stored cleartext pubkeys — a storage-write attacker cannot swap in a wrong pubkey and silently break scanning. Mismatch throws `SessionIntegrityError`; a bad password throws `WrongPasswordError`."},"896":{"id":"sdk-44","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Method"},"897":{"id":"sdk-45","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Purpose"},"898":{"id":"sdk-46","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"`health()`"},"899":{"id":"sdk-47","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Status, balance, address"},"900":{"id":"sdk-48","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"`relay(xdr, opts?)`"},"901":{"id":"sdk-49","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Fee-bump and submit a signed envelope"},"902":{"id":"sdk-50","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"`sponsor(address, opts?)`"},"903":{"id":"sdk-51","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Create a stealth account from the relayer's balance"},"904":{"id":"sdk-52","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"`sponsorClaimPrepare(args)`"},"905":{"id":"sdk-53","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Build the sponsored claim tx (returns unsigned XDR)"},"906":{"id":"sdk-54","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"`sponsorClaimSubmit(xdr, args)`"},"907":{"id":"sdk-55","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Co-sign + submit a sponsored claim"},"908":{"id":"sdk-56","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"`creditClaim(fundingAccount, txHash)`"},"909":{"id":"sdk-57","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Top up credit by proving an XLM payment"},"910":{"id":"sdk-58","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"`creditBalance(fundingAccount)`"},"911":{"id":"sdk-59","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Read a credit balance"},"912":{"id":"sdk-60","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#relayerclient","content":"Also exported: `challengeMessage(endpoint, fundingAccount, nonce, amount, bind?)` — the canonical proof-of-control message, which must match the relayer byte-for-byte. See Relayer."},"913":{"id":"sdk-61","page_id":"sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/sdk#typed-errors","content":"All exported from `