Horizon (send not confirmed?)"],[319,"Stealth address"],[245,"Stealth address holding the funds"],[279,"Stealth address to withdraw from"],[10,"Stellar Asset Contract (SAC)"],[689,"Stellar charges a &#x2A;*minimum balance reserve (MBR)** of \\~1 XLM for every account that exists. A naive stealth-address implementation creates one account per payment and locks \\~1 XLM in each. On chains where accounts are free or negligible, that's fine; on Stellar it makes per-payment accounts impractical."],[370,"Stellar's smart-contract environment doesn't offer the specific curve operation the ECDH needs, so that math runs **on your device**, not on-chain. The contract never sees your keys — it only checks a signature."],[840,"Step-by-step lives in `packages/relayer/README.md`."],[63,"Storage is keyed, never a growing list — so a deposit's cost does **not** scale with history:"],[6,"Storage layout"],[933,"Stored pubkey ≠ pubkey derived from decrypted private key"],[951,"Submission stayed PENDING past the timeout — carries `.txHash` and `.retryable = false`; the tx **may still land**, so poll the hash, do NOT blindly resubmit"],[257,"Sweep the whole account via `AccountMerge` (account method)"],[886,"Takes a `Payment` returned from `scan` and branches on its `method`: `'pool'` → signed withdraw; `'account'` → sweep / partial payout / sponsored claim."],[647,"Testnet"],[603,"Tests"],[683,"That *a* payment happened, or its amount."],[852,"The @shade/sdk and @shade/crypto API: StealthClient, types, typed errors, Freighter signing, encrypted sessions and the stealth-address primitives."],[335,"The **private** spend + view keys stay *with you*: the private view key **detects** incoming payments, the private spend key **spends** them."],[334,"The **public** spend + view keys go *into the meta-address you give out*, so a sender can do the math to create your one-time address."],[344,"The **view tag** is a single byte — `SHA256(S)[0]` — published alongside each announcement. It's a fast-path filter: if the tag doesn't match, the announcement definitely isn't yours and you can skip the rest of the check."],[112,"The `account` method never touches the contract:"],[553,"The `pool` method is enabled but no contract id resolved. There is a built-in default only for `local`."],[30,"The `shade` reference command-line tool."],[470,"The 0.5 XLM claimable-balance reserve returns to the **sender** when the balance is claimed."],[381,"The 32-byte `R`"],[385,"The 32-byte derived stealth public key"],[214,"The amount is parsed to exact stroops **before** any float math, so more than 7 decimal places or an out-of-range value is rejected up front rather than drifting."],[612,"The CLI and SDK are published to npm:"],[301,"The CLI keeps state under `~/.stealth/`:"],[764,"The client attaches its stealth signature and returns the XDR. The relayer then rebuilds the expected operation list from the **trusted inputs** and compares field-by-field (type, per-op source, destination, asset, amount, balanceId, sponsoredId) before adding its own signature. A client cannot mutate any operation and still pass. It also enforces a per-op fee cap (200 stroops/op), the advertised 60-second TTL, and a no-memo rule."],[1027,"The client re-derives the expected operation list from its own trusted inputs and refuses to sign a mismatch (`SponsoredClaimMismatchError`)."],[773,"The client signs the canonical message with the funding account's key:"],[38,"The contract exposes seven functions — two that write, five read-only:"],[86,"The contract moves value through the standard token interface (`soroban_sdk::token::Client`), so it works with any **Stellar Asset Contract** — the contract that exposes a classic Stellar asset (native XLM, USDC, any issued asset) to Soroban. Cross-contract calls are limited to these SAC `transfer` calls:"],[710,"The credit system"],[1068,"The cryptography gives you the tools; you can still deanonymize yourself:"],[967,"The delivery adapters, if you need them directly"],[627,"The demo takes roughly 3 minutes and exercises the whole system:"],[445,"The deposit and its announcement are written **atomically** — no deposit, no announcement — which makes announcement spam impossible."],[563,"The deposit hasn't landed/indexed yet — wait and rescan."],[566,"The destination doesn't (or can't yet) trust the asset you're claiming. &#x2A;*Add the trustline on the destination account before claiming.** If the destination doesn't exist at all, fund it first."],[621,"The examples below use `--network local` (the Docker network from Running from source); substitute `--network testnet` once you've deployed a contract there."],[601,"The fastest path: run the demo"],[685,"The flow of funds. Shade is **not a mixer**: a pool deposit and its withdrawal both name the same stealth key on-chain."],[310,"The keystore itself defaults to `~/.shade-keys.json`."],[712,"The ledger"],[626,"The local network is the `stellar/quickstart:testing` image run with `--local`, exposed on port `8000`."],[322,"The math"],[575,"The meta-address failed prefix, length, hex, checksum, or on-curve/torsion validation. Check for a truncated or mistyped copy-paste."],[556,"The method isn't in `config.methods`. Add it: `methods: ['pool', 'account']`."],[383,"The one-byte fast-path filter (stored as `u32`)"],[562,"The payment isn't yours."],[762,"The payout rides in the same transaction because a stealth account created with `startingBalance: '0'` under sponsorship can never pay a fee to move the tokens itself. It also verifies up front that the destination exists and already trusts the asset."],[4,"The pool contract"],[305,"The pool contract address"],[614,"The pool method needs the stealth pool contract deployed on your target network."],[968,"The primitives, if you're not using the SDK:"],[657,"The problem: your address is a glass mailbox"],[584,"The proof-of-control challenge failed: an expired/unknown nonce (120-second TTL, single-use), an account mismatch, a signature that doesn't verify, or an `authAmount` that doesn't equal what the relayer will charge. On `/relay` the signature also binds the **inner-tx hash** and the network passphrase — a mismatch there fails too. Fetch a fresh nonce and re-sign."],[1004,"The protocol and this implementation have **not undergone an external cryptographic audit**. An audit is on the roadmap. Treat the library as production-track but pre-audit, and **do not handle mainnet value**."],[698,"The protocol and this implementation have **not undergone an external cryptographic audit**. Treat the project as production-track but pre-audit, and do not put mainnet value at risk. Read Security before going further."],[574,"The public key stored in the clear doesn't match the one re-derived from the decrypted private key — **the stored session may have been tampered with**. Don't trust the material; re-import your keys."],[991,"The raw-scalar footgun"],[768,"The relayer checks Horizon: the transaction succeeded, is sourced by that funding account, contains native payment ops **to the relayer** whose op-source is the funding account, and hasn't already been claimed. It sums every qualifying payment op and credits that amount."],[834,"The relayer is deployed from a clone of the Shade repository:"],[765,"The relayer is metered so it isn't a free-for-all:"],[721,"The relayer is the reference service (`packages/relayer`) that an app or community runs. It solves a chicken-and-egg problem: to claim your money you'd normally need a funded Stellar account to pay the fee — but *using* a funded account links it to you, undoing the privacy."],[622,"The relayer pays your withdrawal fee so you never reveal a funded account of your own. It isn't published to npm — run it from a checkout of the repo:"],[583,"The relayer runs with `RELAYER_REQUIRE_CREDIT=1`. Top up via `POST /credit/claim` with the hash of an XLM payment to the relayer, and pass `fundingAccount` (CLI: `--funding-account`) on your requests."],[835,"The relayer ships ready for Railway (`packages/relayer/railway.json`: NIXPACKS build, `npm run start` → `node dist/index.js`, health check on `/health`)."],[774,"The relayer verifies the signature, then **consumes** the nonce."],[572,"The RPC returned a non-terminal status (e.g. `TRY_AGAIN_LATER`) — **nothing landed on-chain**. Safe to retry with a fresh submission. The error carries `.retryable`."],[387,"The SAC token address that was deposited"],[410,"The same meta-address works with more than one \"delivery method\" — the mechanism that actually carries money to the recipient. They differ in where funds sit, what they cost, and how you claim them. This page compares them and tells you which to pick."],[637,"The script builds the contract, deploys it, and writes the resulting contract id where the CLI will find it."],[89,"The SDK resolves an asset string to its SAC address with `resolveTokenAddress`, and `labelForToken` reverses the deterministic native-XLM SAC id back to the label `XLM` for display."],[704,"The Shade relayer: fee-bumping, sponsored claims and the credit system — endpoints, proof-of-control auth, configuration and operational warnings."],[775,"The signed message binds the endpoint, the account, the nonce, and the exact **amount** authorized. On `/relay`, `bind` is additionally the **inner transaction hash**, so an intercepted `{nonce, signature}` cannot be paired with a different inner XDR of the same fee."],[83,"The signed message must be byte-identical between Rust and TypeScript:"],[36,"The Soroban pool contract (`StealthPoolContract`), Rust / `soroban-sdk`."],[565,"The stealth account isn't on Horizon yet — usually the funding send hasn't confirmed. Wait and retry."],[560,"The stealth address holds nothing in the pool **for that asset**. Either it was already withdrawn, or you're querying the wrong asset — pass the right `--asset` / `opts.asset`."],[399,"The three slots"],[84,"The trailing **contract address** and **network id** (= `SHA-256(network passphrase)`, matching the on-chain `env.ledger().network_id()`) bind the signature to a single deployment on a single network, preventing cross-deployment and cross-network replay."],[1015,"The view key can find payments but never move them — safe to delegate to a scanner."],[8,"The withdraw message"],[1017,"The withdraw message binds the contract address **and** the network id, so a signature valid on one deployment is rejected on another."],[452,"The withdrawal **destination must be an existing Stellar account** (it needs its own reserve to exist)."],[623,"Then pass `--relay http://localhost:3000` to `claim`/`withdraw`. See Relayer for endpoints, credit gating, and deployment."],[619,"There is deliberately **no built-in testnet address** — testnet resets periodically, and a stale placeholder would only produce an opaque Soroban failure later. For testnet you must deploy and save the id yourself. Building the contract Wasm requires a checkout of the repo (see Running from source):"],[477,"There is deliberately **no implicit default**: every `send()` must pass a method (or `'auto'`), or it throws `MethodRequiredError`. The privacy trade-off should always be a conscious choice."],[759,"There is deliberately **no sponsorship sandwich** here: `EndSponsoringFutureReserves` must be signed by the sponsored account, whose key nobody holds at creation time. The sandwich lives only in `/sponsor-claim`, where the client holds the stealth key and co-signs."],[552,"There is deliberately no implicit default — the privacy trade-off must be a conscious choice. Pass `method` (CLI: `--method`). Use `'auto'` to let the client pick."],[673,"This distinction is the single most important thing to understand:"],[343,"This is **ECDH** (Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman) — the standard trick that lets two parties arrive at the same secret without ever transmitting it. `S` is what makes the stealth address derivable by you and nobody else."],[191,"This is the safe answer to \"I lost my meta-address\" — as opposed to re-running `shade keygen`, which would overwrite the keys (and now refuses to without `--force`)."],[722,"This page covers what it does, its endpoints, the credit system, configuration, and deployment."],[149,"This page documents every command's real arguments and flags."],[667,"This page explains what Shade is, the problem it solves, and who it's for. If you want to start using it, jump to Getting Started."],[1074,"This project is pre-audit and provided as-is."],[987,"Threat model"],[674,"Three terms first, so the table below reads cleanly. Full definitions are in Core Concepts:"],[915,"Thrown when"],[880,"Throws &#x2A;*`ContractIdRequiredError`** if `'pool'` is enabled and no contract id resolves — failing loudly here instead of surfacing an opaque Soroban error on the first pool call."],[749,"Timebounds must be present, unexpired, and bounded"],[687,"Timing correlation. Withdraw right after a deposit and the link is obvious."],[486,"To avoid locking \\~1 XLM per payment"],[484,"To claim without ever having a funded account"],[613,"To run the local Stellar network, the end-to-end demo, or build the contract yourself, see Running from source below."],[403,"Tokens (USDC and friends)"],[909,"Top up credit by proving an XLM payment"],[738,"Top up credit by proving an XLM payment via `txHash`"],[62,"Total announcements — a cheap freshness check."],[78,"Total announcements; also the next index."],[509,"Troubleshooting by error"],[806,"Trusted reverse-proxy hops, counted from the right"],[467,"Trustline reserve headroom"],[694,"Two delivery methods — &#x2A;*`pool`** (Soroban contract; works with any **SAC** token, i.e. any asset exposed to Soroban via a *Stellar Asset Contract&#x2A; — native XLM, USDC, anything issued) and &#x2A;*`account`** (a direct one-time Stellar account, or a *claimable balance* — a pending transfer the recipient later claims). See Delivery Methods."],[80,"Two different mechanisms, deliberately:"],[1053,"Two hard rules:"],[317